{
  "texts": [
    "By integrating fast-changing forces with a small time step and slow-changing ones with a larger time step, significant performance gains can be achieved without compromising accuracy.",
    "Having proven their usefulness for classical force fields simulations, MTS schemes have been shown to be also applicable to Ab Initio MD (AIMD).",
    "25 In the context of machine learning molecular simulations, few works were reported in that direction.",
    "[26] [27] [28] [29] Thus, MTS schemes are not presently part of today's NNPs toolkit.",
    "Indeed, in their case, force decomposition is not naturally given by physical interactions and naive MTS implementations can be plagued by various sources of instabilities, for example resonances."
  ]
}